<div style="padding:0px 0px 6px 0px"><table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center"><tr><td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" ><a name="post43558"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/tdg/statusicon/post_old.gif" alt="Old" border="0" /></a> 01-14-2003, 09:37 AM</td><td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" align="right">&nbsp;#<a href="showpost.php?s=0ae560748df707a3dc376beb25709ebc&amp;p=43558&amp;postcount=1" target="new"><strong>1</strong></a></td></tr><tr valign="top"><td class="alt2" width="175"><div id="postmenu_43558">Sinjiin</div><div class="smallfont">Guest</div><div class="smallfont">&nbsp;<br /><div>Posts: n/a</div><div>   </div></div></td><td class="alt1"><div class="smallfont"> 	<strong>Healing our FD pullers</strong></div><hr size="1" style="color:" /><div><br /> Since the release of Tunare's Renewal I have been asked to be the main healer of some pick up groups, something I haven't done since around level 30.  Anyway, I am looking for some info/advice on healing our groups puller when using FD.<br />
<br />
If my monk/sk/necro pulls and is FD with mobs near him or her, I don't want to heal them, correct?  Should I wait for them to tell me to heal them?  Sometimes I see their FD fail and they are close to dieing, should I let them die?  These are real noob questions but then again the last time I was the only healer in a group was when I was a noob so I'm looking for suggestions.<br />
 <br /></div></td></tr><tr><td class="alt2"> 	 &nbsp;</td><td class="alt1" align="right"><a href="newreply.php?s=0ae560748df707a3dc376beb25709ebc&amp;do=newreply&amp;p=43558"><img src="images/tdg/buttons/quote.gif" alt="Reply With Quote" border="0" /></a> 	</td></tr></table><div class="vbmenu_popup" id="postmenu_43558_menu" style="display:none"><table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"><tr><td class="thead">Sinjiin</td></tr></table></div></div>
