	<div align="center">
		<div class="page" style="width:100%; text-align:left">
			<div style="padding:0px 25px 0px 25px">
<div style="padding:0px 0px 6px 0px"><table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center"><tr><td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" ><a name="post43560"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/tdg/statusicon/post_old.gif" alt="Old" border="0" /></a> 01-14-2003, 10:30 AM</td><td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" align="right">&nbsp;#<a href="showpost.php?s=0ae560748df707a3dc376beb25709ebc&amp;p=43560&amp;postcount=3" target="new"><strong>3</strong></a></td></tr><tr valign="top"><td class="alt2" width="175"><div id="postmenu_43560">Bizitt</div><div class="smallfont">Guest</div><div class="smallfont">&nbsp;<br /><div>Posts: n/a</div><div>   </div></div></td><td class="alt1"><div><br /> You can heal a monk/sk/nec whenever they have successfully FD'ed and are still down. If a mob isn't beating on them, they have no aggro. They may still have aggro when they get back up, but as long as your heal doesn't land right when they get up, you'll be ok.<br />
<br />
If you don't want aggro (and I specify this because sometimes warriors/SKs/pallys (the "tank") will deliberately heal/buff a puller on incoming to take the mobs' attention), don't heal when the puller is returning to camp with the mobs or the feign has failed. It sucks, yes, but if the puller has too many mobs, you will have to let him or her die. Most pullers accept this risk as part of their job. <br />
<br />
The safest way to go about it is to arrange for your puller to ask for a heal when it's safe (i.e., they're successfully FD). Another strategy that's sometimes used is deliberately taking aggro with a heal while they're not feigned/if feign failed and then kiting the mobs around your group for someone to peel off (obviously this only works in certain hunting grounds and for certain mobs). <br /></div></td></tr><tr><td class="alt2"> 	 &nbsp;</td><td class="alt1" align="right"><a href="newreply.php?s=0ae560748df707a3dc376beb25709ebc&amp;do=newreply&amp;p=43560"><img src="images/tdg/buttons/quote.gif" alt="Reply With Quote" border="0" /></a> 	</td></tr></table><div class="vbmenu_popup" id="postmenu_43560_menu" style="display:none"><table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"><tr><td class="thead">Bizitt</td></tr></table></div></div>
		</div>	
