	<div align="center">
		<div class="page" style="width:100%; text-align:left">
			<div style="padding:0px 25px 0px 25px">
<div style="padding:0px 0px 6px 0px"><table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center"><tr><td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" ><a name="post43562"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/tdg/statusicon/post_old.gif" alt="Old" border="0" /></a> 01-14-2003, 09:36 PM</td><td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" align="right">&nbsp;#<a href="showpost.php?s=0ae560748df707a3dc376beb25709ebc&amp;p=43562&amp;postcount=5" target="new"><strong>5</strong></a></td></tr><tr valign="top"><td class="alt2" width="175"><div id="postmenu_43562">Tiane</div><div class="smallfont">Guest</div><div class="smallfont">&nbsp;<br /><div>Posts: n/a</div><div>   </div></div></td><td class="alt1"><div><br /> Speaking as a part time monk, the safest thing to do is just ask your fd puller.  As a healer, couple tips...  make sure you can see them before you heal... they may be a bit off trying a split or something, but if you see them back at your camp and starting to fight, chances are it's ok to heal.  Also, dont assume that a successful FD means you can heal right away... there may be spells being cast by the mob's that, when they land, will break the FD, and if you healed, you'll be on the aggro list.<br />
<br />
When I'm pulling on my monk, I have a hotkey that says to the group when I use my mend, and another hotkey for Ok to heal.  Dont be afraid to ask your puller to do something similar, as a mistake can lead to a wipe.<br />
<br />
Tia<br />
