<div style="padding:0px 0px 6px 0px"><table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center"><tr><td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" ><a name="post43563"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/tdg/statusicon/post_old.gif" alt="Old" border="0" /></a> 01-15-2003, 06:17 AM</td><td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" align="right">&nbsp;#<a href="showpost.php?s=0ae560748df707a3dc376beb25709ebc&amp;p=43563&amp;postcount=6" target="new"><strong>6</strong></a></td></tr><tr valign="top"><td class="alt2" width="175"><div id="postmenu_43563">Milesgond</div><div class="smallfont">Guest</div><div class="smallfont">&nbsp;<br /><div>Posts: n/a</div><div>   </div></div></td><td class="alt1"><div><br /> try stacking replenishment and natures recovery on the puller.  55 hp per tick is nice little regen.  natures recovery isn't useful very often, but I've found casting it on the FD puller can be helpful sometimes..  it's a pain how often you have to recast it, but if you get in the habit of recasting it every other pull or so it isn't so bad.  I like to use it anyway <img src="http://thedruidsgrove.org/forums/images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" />     of course if they're pulling mobs that hit for 500+ it's not going to make much difference <img src="http://thedruidsgrove.org/forums/images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" />   <br /></div></td></tr><tr><td class="alt2"> 	 &nbsp;</td><td class="alt1" align="right"><a href="newreply.php?s=0ae560748df707a3dc376beb25709ebc&amp;do=newreply&amp;p=43563"><img src="images/tdg/buttons/quote.gif" alt="Reply With Quote" border="0" /></a> 	</td></tr></table><div class="vbmenu_popup" id="postmenu_43563_menu" style="display:none"><table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"><tr><td class="thead">Milesgond</td></tr></table></div></div>
