			<div style="padding:0px 25px 0px 25px">
<table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center"><tr><td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" ><a name="post43564"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/tdg/statusicon/post_old.gif" alt="Old" border="0" /></a> 01-16-2003, 01:59 AM</td><td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" align="right">&nbsp;#<a href="showpost.php?s=0ae560748df707a3dc376beb25709ebc&amp;p=43564&amp;postcount=7" target="new"><strong>7</strong></a></td></tr><tr valign="top"><td class="alt2" width="175"><div id="postmenu_43564">Bjond</div><div class="smallfont">Guest</div><div class="smallfont">&nbsp;<br /><div>Posts: n/a</div><div>   </div></div></td><td class="alt1"><div class="smallfont"> 	<strong>As long as the spell lands ..</strong></div><hr size="1" style="color:" /><div><br /> .. while the monk is actually FD, you will not inherit any agro.  However, if the FD failed (fallen to ground), or if the FD was broken (MOB spell or fist hit monk after monk FD'd), or if the monk stands up just before your spell hits, then you WILL earn agro.  If the monk has to re-FD after any of that, you have just trained your group.<br />
<br />
As a monk, I generally do not want ANY healing, buffing, or songs running while I'm working a rough pull that requires a split.  I expect everyone to watch me die rather than kill themselves by trying to heal me.  Once I have the critter back to the group and I stop and start hitting it, then heal.  Make sure your monk is actually stopped and is fighting.<br />
<br />
Sometimes the pathing will be very buggy and so the monk might look like he's got a single and is running it to the group, but will turn around and then run back to check pathing and FD for the single to proximity agro in to the group.  The pathing is really only this bad in some Luclin areas.  Not sure on Pop, but from what I've seen so far PoP might be worse.<br />
<br />
IMHO, any xp spot that requires more than a couple FD's at the opening to perhaps space a spawn isn't worth the effort.  FD-split is a complete waste of time.  Much better XP is to be had from any zone where you can level pull or sneak toss something your group can handle. <br /></div></td></tr><tr><td class="alt2"> 	 &nbsp;</td><td class="alt1" align="right"><a href="newreply.php?s=0ae560748df707a3dc376beb25709ebc&amp;do=newreply&amp;p=43564"><img src="images/tdg/buttons/quote.gif" alt="Reply With Quote" border="0" /></a> 	</td></tr></table><div class="vbmenu_popup" id="postmenu_43564_menu" style="display:none"><table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"><tr><td class="thead">Bjond</td></tr></table></div>
